				Alchemy's Moulton sees distressed opportunities ahead


April 25, 2006





From 
				Reuters:

Opportunities to buy 
				distressed companies or their debt are opening up and will 
				continue to do so as economies worsen amid the global credit 
				crunch, a leading buyout executive said on Friday.

				Highly indebted companies in cyclical industries such as 
				construction, real estate and retail are likely to struggle to 
				make interest payments, making their debt trade at a discount in 
				the secondary market, or cutting the value of the equity.




Source   
				                                                                                          
				  

