				was taking as collateral for a $30bn (19bn) loan to Bear 
				Stearns, US-listed asset manager BlackRock was the obvious 
				choice.

				By the admission of its rivals, BlackRock is one of fewer than 
				half a dozen asset managers with the expertise and resources to 
				take on such an assignment, alongside Pimco, Western Asset 
				Managers and Goldman Sachs Asset Management.




