				Distressed Investing Opportunities in the Middle Markets, More 
				at iiBIG New York City Forum


March 13, 2006





From 
				Marketwire:

Headlines are 
				dominated by names like "Blackstone" and "Carlyle" but the 
				meat-and-potatoes of the distressed investing business are in 
				the middle markets -- the focus of iiBIG's Distressed & 
				Turnaround Investment Forum EAST, scheduled for May 14-15, 2008 
				in New York City.

				The credit crunch is no doubt having an impact on the buy-out 
				markets, particularly at the high-end of the scale -- deals in 
				$2 billion-and-up category. But with those larger deals becoming 
				harder to do, even the larger funds -- and others with 
				"dry-powder" -- are focusing on distressed investments in the 
				middle-markets where transaction activity remains strong and 
				lucrative deals are being done. 





