'Vultures' Circle, Warily


November 30, 2006





From 
				The Wall Street Journal Online:

With its purchase 
				this week of assets from mortgage lender E*Trade Financial 
				Corp., Citadel Investment Group seemed to signal a rising 
				investor appetite for distressed securities and provide a 
				possible indication that a bottom in the mortgage crisis could 
				be nearing.

				Not so fast. The "vulture" market, as it is known, is now flush 
				with cash. By some estimates, such funds have raised more than 
				$600 billion in recent years, much of it accumulated recently to 
				pounce on opportunities created by mortgage-market turmoil. But 
				many of them are keeping their powder dry.




