Vultures Swoop In 
				On Builders' Land


November 9, 2006





From 
				TheStreet.com:

Real estate vulture 
				funds are scouring the U.S. for distressed housing developments 
				and land sites being sold at cheap prices by homebuilders 
				looking to clean up their balance sheets.

				These funds, which target internal rates of return greater than 
				20%, are not betting on any immediate recovery in housing. 
				Instead, they're seeing profit in buying the housing sites today 
				--many of which are selling at 50% or greater below their peak 
				2005 values -- with the aim of flipping them or selling homes at 
				the projects in two years or more. 




