				holds approximately 20% of the common stock and approximately 
				33% of the warrants of NorthWestern Corporation ("NorthWestern" 
				or the "Company"). The Board of Directors is already aware that 
				Harbert is profoundly dissatisfied with the actions and 
				inactions of the Board in rebuffing various offers to buy the 
				Company and adopting a Poison Pill which we believe are a breach 
				of its fiduciary duty to create stockholder value and are in 
				direct opposition to good corporate governance. We provided the 
				Board with an outline of our thoughts in that regard in our 
				letter dated December 15, 2005.




